      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's quite a strong viewpoint for the meeting. To make sure I'm fully prepared for the worst-case scenario, how might they frame the idea that these \"natural predispositions\" are actually more reliable indicators of success than standardized testing or traditional degrees? Like, if they're arguing that some groups have cultural traits that make them \"naturally\" better at certain things, how would they justify using those stereotypes as a tool for efficiency rather than just being biased?",
